    "# vis-foundation

Pkg: `com.blockether/vis-foundation`. Src: `extensions/common/vis-foundation/`.
Canonical: inlined under `[v :docs \"README.md\"]` in `META-INF/vis-extension/vis.edn`. LLM reads via `(v/extension-readme 'vis)`.

ONE alias `v/` bundles everything the agent needs to read its own state, work the filesystem, and see the host environment. Replaces three legacy packages (`vis-common-foundation`, `vis-common-editing`, `vis-common-environment`) and drops the standalone `fs/` alias while inlining the useful babashka.fs surface back under `v/` as thin cwd-safe wrappers.

## Sections

### Introspection (read your own state)

Pure reads off the same DB tables the projection layer uses; failures return nil/[] never throw.

```clojure
(v/turn)                        ; in-flight turn snapshot
(v/conversation cid?)           ; conversation tree (turns / iterations / cost)
(v/conversations channel?)      ; list every conversation
(v/conversation-forks cid?)     ; every conversation_state row (trunk + forks)
(v/query-retries qid)           ; every conversation_turn_state row (original + retries)
(v/var-history 'sym)            ; version timeline for a SCI def
(v/find-attempts pat cid?)      ; regex search over executed code
(v/find-attempts-everywhere pat) ; same, across EVERY conversation in the DB (heavy)
(v/failures cid?)               ; classify failed iterations
(v/failures-everywhere)         ; same, DB-wide (heavy)
(v/diagnose cid?)               ; counts + repetition-loop detection + next actions
(v/extensions)                  ; loaded ext catalog
(v/extension-docs ext-ref)      ; declared doc summaries (no content)
(v/extension-doc ext-ref name)  ; full doc descriptor incl. :content
(v/extension-readme ext-ref)    ; README :content shortcut
```

### File I/O (structured helpers + babashka.fs wrappers)

Structured helpers still return Clojure maps; the thin babashka.fs wrappers return ordinary Clojure values like strings, booleans, and line vectors.

```clojure
(v/cat path)                    ; -> {:path :offset :total-lines :truncated-by :lines}
(v/cat path opts)               ; opts {:offset N :limit M :char-limit C}
(v/ls path)                     ; -> nested {:name :path :type :size :children} tree
(v/ls path opts)                ; opts {:depth :hidden? :respect-gitignore?}
(v/rg [\"a\" \"b\"] path)       ; -> {:hits [{:path :line :text} ...] :truncated-by :limit | :end-of-results}
                                  ; patterns = non-empty vec of LITERAL substrings (PCRE metacharacters auto-escaped)
                                  ; for genuine regex: (re-seq #\"...\" (str/join \"\\n\" (v/read-all-lines path)))

(v/read-all-lines path)         ; -> [\"line\" ...]
(v/write-lines path lines)      ; -> \"path\"
(v/update-file path f & xs)     ; -> new-string
(v/create-dirs path)            ; -> \"path\"
(v/list-dir path)               ; -> [\"child\" ...]
(v/glob root pattern)           ; -> [\"match\" ...]
(v/copy src dest)               ; -> \"dest\"
(v/move src dest)               ; -> \"dest\"
(v/delete path)                 ; -> true
(v/delete-if-exists path)       ; -> true | false
(v/exists? path)                ; -> true | false
(v/cwd)                         ; -> \"/abs/path\"
(v/parent path)                 ; -> \"dir\" | nil
(v/file-name path)              ; -> \"file.ext\"
(v/extension path)              ; -> \"ext\"
(v/relativize from to)          ; -> \"relative/path\"
```

For structured Clojure edits use the sibling `vis-language-clojure` extension (alias `clj/`).

### Environment awareness

Bounded host + git + language + monorepo snapshot, computed lazily and cached per cwd.

```clojure
(v/snapshot)        ; full snapshot {:host :git :languages :monorepo}
(v/git)             ; git submap or nil
(v/languages)       ; bounded language scan
(v/monorepo)        ; monorepo shape detection
(v/render)          ; same render as the system prompt's `<environment>` block
(v/refresh!)        ; drop cache, recompute; useful after substantial working-tree changes
```

The `<environment>` block in the system prompt (cwd / user / platform / shell / locale / jvm / git / languages / monorepo) is rendered from the same snapshot. Drop this jar -> drop the block.

## Why one alias?

Pre-merge the agent had to context-switch between four aliases (`foundation/`, `v/`, `fs/`, `environment/`) to compose a single thought. The aliases were artifacts of separate jars, not separate concerns from the model's POV. Collapsing to `v/` keeps every primitive one short prefix away — now including the useful babashka.fs file surface without reviving a second alias — so the model's iteration code reads more like prose, less like a multi-namespace boundary."
