   {:created-at #inst "2026-04-29T00:00:00.000-00:00"
    :description
    "md/: pure string builders for `(answer …)` bodies. Headings, emphasis, lists, tables, code blocks, link helpers (`md/link` `md/image` `md/file-link` `md/anchor`). Composers (`md/join` `md/lines`) splice sequential collections one level. Strings everywhere — sequential collections in scalar slots throw."
    :content
    "# md — markdown builders\n\nPkg: `com.blockether/vis-foundation` (sibling alias `v/`).\nSrc: `extensions/common/vis-foundation/src/com/blockether/vis/ext/foundation/markdown.clj`.\nDocs: `docs/src/extensions/common/markdown.md` (mdBook).\nLLM read: `(v/extension-readme 'md)`.\n\nOne path to an answer body: pure string builders -> `(answer …)` ships verbatim.\n\n## Surface\n\n```clojure\n;; Headings\n(md/h1 s) (md/h2 s) (md/h3 s) (md/h4 s) (md/h5 s) (md/h6 s)\n(md/h n s)                         ; n clamped to [1,6]\n\n;; Inline\n(md/bold s) (md/italic s) (md/bold-italic s)\n(md/strike s) (md/code s) (md/kbd s)\n\n;; Links / images / citations — use these for every clickable jump\n(md/link text url)                ; [text](url)\n(md/link text url title)          ; + tooltip\n(md/image alt url)\n(md/image alt url title)\n(md/file-link path)               ; [src/foo.clj](src/foo.clj)\n(md/file-link path line)          ; [src/foo.clj:142](src/foo.clj#L142)\n(md/anchor text)\n(md/anchor text slug)\n\n;; Blocks\n(md/p s)                          ; paragraph\n(md/code-block s)                 ; ``` fence\n(md/code-block s \"clojure\")     ; ```clojure fence\n(md/blockquote s)\nmd/hr md/br                       ; constants\n(md/details summary body)\n\n;; Lists\n(md/li parts...)                  ; single list item: \"- text\"\n(md/ul items) (md/ol items)\n(md/checklist [[\"done\" true] [\"todo\" false]])\n\n;; Tables\n(md/table headers rows)\n(md/table headers rows {:align [:left :center :right]})\n\n;; Compose\n(md/join   block-or-coll …)       ; blank line between; splices seqs 1 level\n(md/lines  line-or-coll  …)       ; single newline; splices seqs 1 level\n(md/section title body)           ; h2 + body\n(md/section level title body)\n(md/escape s)                     ; backslash-escape commonmark specials\n```\n\n## Procedural rules\n\n1. Block fn -> string without trailing newline. Compose via `(md/join …)`.\n2. Cite source -> `(md/file-link path line)`. Channels render the jump.\n3. URL / diagram -> `(md/link text url \"tooltip\")` / `(md/image alt url \"tooltip\")`. In-doc jump -> `(md/anchor text)`. Always go through helpers — they stay aligned with channel link conventions.\n4. Scalar slot (`md/p`, `md/h1`, table cell, list item) takes string-coercible value: string, keyword, number. Sequential collection in a scalar slot throws ex-info: `\"sequential collection where a string was expected\"`. Build the row eagerly, then splice via `md/join`.\n5. Compose-slot collections: `md/join` and `md/lines` splice sequential args one level. `(md/join (mapv render xs))` and `(md/join (md/h1 \"…\") (mapv render xs))` both work.\n6. EAGER builders only — evaluate sequences before they reach a builder. Use `mapv`, `keep`, `into [] (map f) xs`, `reduce`, `for` wrapped in `vec`. Lazy seqs (`map`, `filter`, raw `for`) stringify as `clojure.lang.LazySeq@<hex>` if they leak into a scalar slot — eager forms make that impossible by construction.\n\n```clojure\n;; Eager-only forms\n(mapv render-turn turns)                       ; vector of rows\n(into []  (map  render-turn) turns)            ; vector via xform\n(into []  (keep render-maybe) turns)           ; vector, drops nils\n(reduce   (fn [acc t] (conj acc (render t))) [] turns)\n(vec (for [t turns] (render-turn t)))          ; eager `for` -> vector\n```\n\n## Example\n\n```clojure\n(answer\n  (md/join\n    (md/h1 \"Patch report\")\n    (md/p \"Three files touched.\")\n    (md/table [\"file\" \"+/-\"]\n              [[(md/file-link \"src/core.clj\") \"+12 / -4\"]\n               [(md/file-link \"src/loop.clj\" 142) \"+0 / -38\"]])\n    (md/h2 \"Next\")\n    (md/ul [\"Run verify.sh\" \"Update CHANGELOG\"])\n    (md/code-block \"(println :done)\" \"clojure\")))\n\n;; Splice rows from a collection\n(answer\n  (md/join\n    (md/h1 (str \"Conversation: \" CONVERSATION_TITLE))\n    (md/p (str \"Turns: \" (count turns)))\n    md/hr\n    (mapv render-turn turns)))                  ; vector spliced one level\n```"
